  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That brings us to 1939.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's correct.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "September 1, 1939, the World War II broke out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And after listening to all the propaganda on how short of a war this will be and how quickly the Poles will win the war, the, the French, the English will enter the war quickly on short notice and Germany will be defeated in no time at all.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we really did not concern ourselves too much.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On the other hand, as I said before, the Jews sort of lived in Poland like in their own world.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were really extremely happy with being permitted to conduct their own lives, their own religious lives.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they didn't worry about politics of the country too much.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so we were not overly anxious when, when war-- World War II broke out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was one of those situations, it's going to start, it's going to end.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And maybe nothing terrible will happen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But after a few days after September 1, 1939, we indeed saw the Germans coming into the city of Krakow.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember going out with other children to greet the German soldiers as they were arriving on their tanks, on their trucks.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they would set up some quarters on the-- along the road.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was in the summer, so they would set up some quarters.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when they began to dish out food, they in fact gave some food to the children that came to see them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I was one of those kids that would receive food from the German soldiers as they were advancing into, into Poland.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But of course, it didn't take very long before the war got uglier.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we, as a family, had to leave our house in Borek Falecki and run from there.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
